import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2 Concentration'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    yearly_avg = data.groupby('year')['co2_concentration'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    yearly_avg.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average CO2 concentration for each year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['CO2_concentration'], data['temperature'])

    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 concentration and temperature?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    data['Month'] = data['Date'].dt.month
    monthly_data = data.groupby('Month')['CO2'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(monthly_data.index, monthly_data.values)
    
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the seasonal pattern of CO2 concentration?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
